betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Welcome to GrindBlock! This is a GregTech and Skyblock modpack. As the name implies, there's a bit of grinding to do on the modpack, so get ready for a bit of grinding!

As a present, here are some starting items for you to work with. Try not to lose the saplings, it'd be embarrasing to lose them this early on

Also make sure you place the Ice ontop of a block so you actually get water!

Also, you can spam your shift key to make trees grow faster.
Wood. It's useful. Need I say more?
Cobblestone is quite useful for base building, as it's fire resistant!
You'll need these to be considered a real Starter Base(tm)
I hope you enjoy stone tools, because you'll probably be using them for a while!
If you're going to build a base, you should definitely be using slabs to do so. Also, Â§lmake sure you build in bottom half slabs so mobs can't spawn on them

It's course.... rough.... irritating.... and it falls in the void!

Thankfully, I've decided that instead, you get the sand island from me, the quest book! Aren't I generous? Click the checkbox if you agree!

Don't lose it, cause I ain't giving you any more sand than this!
It's time for you to go build a platform to kill mobs! Make sure to keep it a bit away from your base!

Once you collect enough iron, make a GregTech hammer. It'll be useful!

Also I hope you have a big enough of a mob farm, or an automatic one!
Kill some spiders and make wool, then make a bed
If you break Cobblestone with the GregTech hammer you just made, you can get Gravel!
betterquesting:10.name:8: I don't have a Gravel joke

betterquesting:10.desc:8: But atleast you can make some now! If you break Gravel with the GregTech hammer, you get some sand!
Did you know you can get iron as a rare drop from Zombies?
If some Witches spawned, you should definitely kill them for Redstone and Glowstone. Both may be useful in the future!

It's time to make wrought iron! You're going to need this soon! Hope you're getting enough iron from your mob farm, cause you'll need a bit of it!

To make Wrought Iron, turn Iron Ingots into Iron Nuggets, then cook the Iron Nuggets in a furnace to get Wrought Iron nuggets, then craft them into an ingot for Wrought Iron
Welcome to what exists of the ULV tier. You'll need these two machines, so get crafty!
Congratulations, you're getting your first bits of ore! You can sift gravel for Flint, Iron, Copper, Silver, Tin, and Redstone! Get me 9 Copper and 3 Tin to prove you're worthy!
It may be delicious, but it's also useful! You'll need some sulfur, so don't forget to sift some sand as well!
No, not the weapon, the GregTech tool. Crush the Copper and Tin down into dust, then make Bronze with it

Place your hammer in your 2x2 and some sand to make dust

Yeah I know you can't break sand into dust right now... (but maybe you can in the future!)
It's time to make clay! What you'll need is some flowing water. Then, place the dust blocks where it'll be touched by water, and voila! It turns into clay! (like concrete powder in vanilla)
You'll need a wrench. It's likely one of the most useful tools in GregTech, so make sure you have one. You can make one with Iron
betterquesting:10.name:8: Throwing a wrench in your plans

betterquesting:10.desc:8: Yes, we're going from ULV to Steam tier. Steam is going to be much better to work with than that inefficient Burner Generator you made earlier. Make a Steam boiler with some Bronze and bricks, now that you can make them

Welcome to the Steam Age, and congratulations if you made it this far! It only gets more grindy from here! Click the checkbox to recieve an awesome prize! I baked these two cakes just for you!

Â§l!!! Â§rÂ§cÂ§lIMPORTANT Â§rÂ§l!!!Â§r

Make sure you place the Overworld cake Â§cÂ§lIN THE NETHERÂ§r otherwise you won't be able to return with your items!!!
Time to go to the nether! What you'll want to do is build to a Nether Fortress (have fun lmao) and get two diamonds in it. I hope the first Nether Fortress you go to has two!
So, you can make steam, time to finally put it to use. Make a Macerator!
You can now macerate Dust for Diamonds!
Why not put some of that steam to use and make an alloy smelter? It'll let you make more bronze from the same amount as dust from handcrafting, and create new things, like Red Alloy!
Well.... not exactly.... but it can compress things!
Provide a Steam Rock Breaker some... well... steam! And put Water and Lava next to it, and voila! It can mine cobblestone for you!
You now have all the necessary machines to make a Primitive Blast Furnace for steel. I would recommend using a Steam Macerator to get the dust you need
